The article highlights the important contributions that veteran business owners make to the American economy. It states that before the pandemic, veteran unemployment was at a record low and veteran-owned small businesses employed millions of people and generated billions of dollars in sales. The article also mentions the strong economic growth and job recovery that is currently taking place, with the economy growing at an impressive rate and jobs being added in sectors that are prominent for veterans. The article praises the dedication, brilliance, and tenacity of veterans and their entrepreneurial spirit in fueling the economic recovery. It concludes by commending veterans for their courage, service, and character, and for being the pride of the nation.